WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:13.512
How do you pick a profit target you'll actually hit,
instead of one that looks amazing on paper and never
fills? This one table is the answer. It's a probability
map for your trade.

2
00:00:14.112 --> 00:00:29.280
It's called MFE Strike Rates. Remember, MFE is the best a
trade runs in your favor before it's over. Every row in
this table is a possible profit target, measured in basis
points. And the strike rate next to it is the share of
your trades that actually reached that target.

3
00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:50.136
Read it from the top. A tiny target, five hundredths of a
percent, gets hit ninety one percent of the time. Almost a
sure thing. Now walk down the rows. The targets get
bigger, and the strike rate keeps falling. By thirty
hundredths of a percent you're at forty one percent, fewer
than half your trades. By half a percent, just nineteen.
That's a lottery ticket, not a plan.

4
00:00:50.736 --> 00:01:08.088
The columns on the right turn that into money. Hits is how
many trades reached the target. Win dollars is what a
single hit pays you there. And potential is the strike
rate times the payout across all your trades. Notice the
trade-off. Bigger targets pay more per hit, but you reach
them less often, and your loss rate climbs.

5
00:01:08.688 --> 00:01:30.816
So here's how you actually choose. Don't chase the biggest
number on the screen. Find the row where the strike rate
is high enough that you'll hit it on most trades, and the
payout is still worth taking. A target up around the
seventy or sixty percent rows banks real money on the
majority of your trades. That's a realistic expectation. A
target you'll reach, not one you'll sit and stare at while
it fades back to red.

6
00:01:31.416 --> 00:01:42.840
Then pair the target you pick here with the stop you
pulled from the MAE side, and you've got both halves of
the trade. A target that's realistic, and a stop that
survives your normal heat. That is the entire point of
this dashboard.

7
00:01:43.440 --> 00:01:50.640
Set your targets by probability, not by hope. The strike
rate tells you the honest truth about what this move will
actually give you.
